      • hasBoundingPoly

        public boolean hasBoundingPoly()
         The bounding polygon around the face. The coordinates of the bounding box
 are in the original image's scale, as returned in `ImageParams`.
 The bounding box is computed to "frame" the face in accordance with human
 expectations. It is based on the landmarker results.
 Note that one or more x and/or y coordinates may not be generated in the
 `BoundingPoly` (the polygon will be unbounded) if only a partial face
 appears in the image to be annotated.
        .google.cloud.vision.v1.BoundingPoly bounding_poly = 1;
        Specified by:
        hasBoundingPoly in interface FaceAnnotationOrBuilder

      • hasFdBoundingPoly

        public boolean hasFdBoundingPoly()
         The `fd_bounding_poly` bounding polygon is tighter than the
 `boundingPoly`, and encloses only the skin part of the face. Typically, it
 is used to eliminate the face from any image analysis that detects the
 "amount of skin" visible in an image. It is not based on the
 landmarker results, only on the initial face detection, hence
 the <code>fd</code> (face detection) prefix.
        .google.cloud.vision.v1.BoundingPoly fd_bounding_poly = 2;
        Specified by:
        hasFdBoundingPoly in interface FaceAnnotationOrBuilder
